3. Findings and Results
This study attempted to develop a coherent understanding about the smart opportunities of AI for reimagining teacher training and the key components for the development of AI-powered teacher education. The analysis of the collected data reveals that AI-powered teacher education can be conceptualized through five components including “intended use of AI in the teacher education context; Machine learning with data monitoring; AI-human interaction; AI feedback for better faculty management; Digital vision, risks and AI ethics”. The five components of AI-powered teacher training are explained in detail with codes and examples in Table 7:


Sustainability 2025, 17, 9815 15 of 35
Table 7. Summary of themes and explanation of codes.
Themes Summary of Themes Codes Examples
Intended use of AI in a teacher education context
The intended use includes making the teacher-training curriculum smarter, preparing different stakeholders for AI readiness, demanding a legal infrastructure for AI in teacher training, and making the teacher hiring process more effective.
AI readiness of stakeholders (benefits equally distributed)
A new recruitment system from AI data analytics (equal and long-term assessment) AI-automated teacher education curriculum (resource-efficient)
Assessment and evaluation performance (unbiased)
Emerging legal basis for AI integration
“As a stakeholder, faculties of education need to adapt to AI and increase their readiness rather than resistance to technology.” AIE 2
“Why not a new recruitment system?, supported by AI data analytics, makes it possible to evaluate candidates’ competencies more objectively and over the years.” M 3 “The course packages of faculties of education are far behind the world. . . . updating the courses at regular intervals would make teacher training programs smarter. ...There is a need for AI-guided course lists in education faculties” CD 1 “Teachers now can make better assessments, for instance AI creates good short essay questions or multiple-choice tests. I read that it can even evaluate written research report like teachers”FM 2 “AI is becoming legalized and public trust. It will increasingly feature in governments’ future plans” AIE1
